{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI","doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/LabeledContent"]]},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/LabeledContent\/multilineTextAlignment(_:)"},"metadata":{"extendedModule":"OpenSwiftUICore","remoteSource":{"fileName":"EnvironmentParagraphStyle.swift","url":"https:\/\/github.com\/OpenSwiftUIProject\/OpenSwiftUI\/blob\/main\/Sources\/OpenSwiftUICore\/View\/Text\/Util\/EnvironmentParagraphStyle.swift#L383"},"title":"multilineTextAlignment(_:)","roleHeading":"Instance Method","modules":[{"relatedModules":["OpenSwiftUICore"],"name":"OpenSwiftUI"}],"role":"symbol","platforms":[{"name":"iOS","introducedAt":"13.0","deprecated":false,"unavailable":false,"beta":false},{"name":"macOS","introducedAt":"10.15","deprecated":false,"unavailable":false,"beta":false},{"name":"tvOS","introducedAt":"13.0","deprecated":false,"unavailable":false,"beta":false},{"name":"visionOS","introducedAt":"1.0","deprecated":false,"unavailable":false,"beta":false},{"name":"watchOS","introducedAt":"6.0","deprecated":false,"unavailable":false,"beta":false}],"externalID":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewPAAE22multilineTextAlignmentyQrAA0fG0OF::SYNTHESIZED::s:11OpenSwiftUI14LabeledContentV","symbolKind":"method","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"multilineTextAlignment"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"TextAlignment","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore13TextAlignmentO"},{"kind":"text","text":") -> "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"some"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"View","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewP"}]},"sections":[],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/openswiftui\/labeledcontent\/multilinetextalignment(_:)"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"attribute","text":"nonisolated"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"multilineTextAlignment"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"_"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"internalParam","text":"alignment"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/TextAlignment","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore13TextAlignmentO","text":"TextAlignment"},{"kind":"text","text":") -> "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"some"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/View","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewP","text":"View"},{"kind":"text","text":"\n"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"parameters":[{"name":"alignment","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"A value that you use to align multiple lines of","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"text within a view.","type":"text"}]}]}],"kind":"parameters"},{"content":[{"type":"heading","anchor":"return-value","level":2,"text":"Return Value"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A view that aligns the lines of multiline "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Text"},{"type":"text","text":" instances"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"it contains."}]}],"kind":"content"},{"content":[{"type":"heading","anchor":"discussion","level":2,"text":"Discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Use this modifier to set an alignment for a multiline block of text.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"For example, the modifier centers the contents of the following","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Text","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" view:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["Text(\"This is a block of text that shows up in a text element as multiple lines.\\(\"\\n\") Here we have chosen to center this text.\")","    .frame(width: 200)","    .multilineTextAlignment(.center)"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The text in the above example spans more than one line because:"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The newline character introduces a line break.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The frame modifier limits the space available to the text view, and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"by default a text view wraps lines that don’t fit in the available"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"width. As a result, the text before the explicit line break wraps to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"three lines, and the text after uses two lines."}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The modifier applies the alignment to the all the lines of text in","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the view, regardless of why wrapping occurs:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The modifier has no effect on a "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Text","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" view that contains only one"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"line of text, because a text view has a width that exactly matches the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"width of its widest line. If you want to align an entire text view"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"rather than its contents, set the aligment of its container, like a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/VStack","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" or a frame that you create with the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/View\/frame(minWidth:idealWidth:maxWidth:minHeight:idealHeight:maxHeight:alignment:)","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"modifier."}]},{"type":"aside","style":"note","name":"Note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can use this modifier to control the alignment of a "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Text","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"view that you create with the "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Text\/init(_:style:)","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" initializer"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to display localized dates and times, including when the view uses"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"only a single line, but only when that view appears in a widget."}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The modifier also affects the content alignment of other text container"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"types, like "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"TextEditor"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"TextField"},{"type":"text","text":". In those cases, the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"modifier sets the alignment even when the view contains only a single"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"line because view’s width isn’t dictated by the width of the text it"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"contains."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The modifier operates by setting the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/EnvironmentValues\/multilineTextAlignment","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" value in the environment,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"so it affects all the text containers in the modified view hierarchy.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"For example, you can apply the modifier to a ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/VStack","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"configure all the text views inside the stack.","type":"text"}]}],"kind":"content"}],"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Sets the alignment of a text view that contains multiple lines of text."}],"references":{"doc://OpenSwiftUI/documentation/OpenSwiftUI/VStack":{"title":"VStack","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"VStack"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A view that arranges its subviews in a vertical line."}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"VStack"}],"kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/VStack","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/openswiftui\/vstack"},"doc://OpenSwiftUI/documentation/OpenSwiftUI":{"kind":"symbol","role":"collection","url":"\/documentation\/openswiftui","type":"topic","title":"OpenSwiftUI","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Declare the user interface and behavior for your app on every platform."}]},"doc://OpenSwiftUI/documentation/OpenSwiftUI/LabeledContent/multilineTextAlignment(_:)":{"title":"multilineTextAlignment(_:)","url":"\/documentation\/openswiftui\/labeledcontent\/multilinetextalignment(_:)","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Sets the alignment of a text view that contains multiple lines of text."}],"type":"topic","role":"symbol